Consent E-mail Security:

Discussion / Observation:
The consent e-mail sent to merchants contains a clickable URL. Concern raised that GIS (security team) may flag this as a spam/phishing link.

Action:
Add OTP validation on URL click for security. OTP sent to merchant email for 2FA. Also  From-email ID is a trusted whitelisted bank address

Consent E-mail – Bank CC:

Discussion / Observation:
Discussed that merchants sometimes miss or ignore the consent e-mail. A bank group e-mail ID should be CC on the consent e-mail so the DO user can re-forward if needed.

Action:
Add a bank group e-mail as CC on all consent e-mails. DO user will re-forward from that mailbox to obtain merchant consent where required.(before URL expiry)

Processing Records Without Consent:

Discussion / Observation:
Current flow blocks DO users from accessing a merchant record until consent is received. Request raised to allow DO users to view all uploaded records regardless of consent status, with a visible flag showing consent state (e.g., Consent Pending / Consent Received).

Action:
New Change Request – Current flow developed as per DIB requirement document shared earlier. Allowing DO enrichment before consent is a workflow change and will be taken as an additional CR. Effort to be estimated and approved before proceeding.


